HEADWORD: Holarctic
<hw>Hol"arc*tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Holo-</ets>
+ <ets>arctic</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pert. to the arctic regions
collectively</def>; specif. <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧geography)</fld>,
<def>designating a realm or region including the northern parts of the
Old and the New World. It comprises the <part>Palearctic</part> and
<part>Nearctic</part> regions or subregions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

